<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-512-637  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 512 637.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  Oct 15 1990 n488 p10(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software AG adds client/server scheme. (Software AG of NorthAmerica Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cortese, Amy.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Software AG of North America Inc is shifting from being amainframe database supplier to a supplier of computer-aidedengineering tools and an application development environment formultivendor platforms.andP;  The company's strategy, called Entire,enables users to build client/server applications that can shareinformation across multiple environments.andP;  The Entire FunctionServer Technology Series of products is based on Software AG'sIntegrated Software Architecture (ISA) and Naturalfourth-generation language.andP;  ISA software, which includes clientapplications and servers, uses various agents to maskplatform-specific details in order for applications to runindependently of the operating system, communications protocol anddatabase.andP;  Software AG will offer its Natural Database ManagementSystem server for database and function services.andP;  In 1991, anOpen SQL server will be available for prominent environments.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Software AG of North America Inc. (management).andO;Topic:     Client/Server ArchitectureIntegrated SoftwareArchitectureMarketing StrategyManagement StyleNatural Language InterfacesFourth-Generation LanguagesOperating EnvironmentsData BasesDistributed Processing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>